Job Title: Senior Digital Business Analyst - Day Rate Contract
Ad Text:
Business Analyst (Digital Platforms)
  
We are partnering with a well-established member organisation with a high-traffic digital platform, focused on delivering seamless and secure online experiences at scale. Looking for an experienced Business Analyst to join a high-performing AEM squad delivering continuous improvement across a large-scale digital platform.
  
This is a hands-on delivery role suited to someone who is comfortable working in fast-moving Agile teams.
  
What you’ll be doing

Work closely with business and technical stakeholders to understand requirements and translate them into user stories, acceptance criteria, and functional specifications
Ensure requirements align with AEM capabilities, architecture, and best practices
Facilitate discovery and refinement sessions with business, UX, developers, content, analytics, and platform teams
Support backlog refinement, sprint planning, and iterative delivery within an Agile squad
Focus on improving content authoring workflows and usability for content teams
Partner with UX and development to ensure designs are technically feasible and scalable
Identify risks, dependencies, and integration requirements early
Ensure solutions meet relevant data governance, security, and compliance standards
  
What we’re looking for

5+ years’ experience as a Business Analyst on complex digital platforms
*Must have* Hands-on AEM experience (authoring, components, templates, workflows)
Strong Agile delivery background within cross-functional squads
Experience working with APIs, integrations, and data-driven solutions
Comfortable working in ambiguity and shifting priorities
Strong facilitation, stakeholder management, and communication skills
Proficiency with Jira, Confluence, and process modelling tools (Visio, draw.io)
 The benefits: 


3 month day rate contract with strong possibility for extension
ASAP start
Hybrid working arrangements - Melbourne offices
Supportive culture with focus on training & development
Strong opportunities for progression into different projects
Access Contractor Benefits Program: Enjoy discounts at hundreds of retail outlets, department stores, activities, novated lease, travel and restaurants nationwide
Get gym membership discounts with our partners
Enjoy Health Insurance discounts off all NIB retail health insurance products
Access EAP for wellbeing and mental health support

If you have teh right skillset, please get in contact with Lainey or send me your resume to lainey.macdonald@halcyonknights.com.au

Job Title: Principal Consultant - Data and Analytics | Brisbane
Ad Text:
Our Purpose

Here at Datacom, we connect people and technology to solve challenges, create opportunities and discover new possibilities for the communities we live in whilst embodying a culture of trust and respect for employees and customers alike.

Our Team

The Data and Analytics team are a progressive group of diverse and creative individuals with a deep love for all things data related. They build platforms and solutions that are leading edge and at the forefront of the technology curve. A close knit and fun team embedded within our rapidly growing Professional Services division, and part of the wider Datacom ecosystem.

About the Role

As a Principal Consultant, you will lead the technical delivery of large-scale data platform and BI solutions. You will be asked to design, implement and own the delivery of robust Data Platform solutions and end-to-end components. This is a client facing role, so you'll need to be an excellent communicator and good with people. The Principal Consultant works closely with practice leads, project managers, scrum masters, and client stakeholders and teams.

What You’ll Do

Working with clients (businesses users) to gather, clarify requirements and business rules by running workshops with stakeholders.
Lead the technical architecture, design and delivery for a new Data platform.
Provide overall thought leadership to our clients regarding data profiling and integration recommendations.
Data modelling (relational and dimensional like star schema and Snowflake schema)
Managing development life cycle using various source code management tools.
Ability to perform performance tuning and optimisation on new and/or existing data warehouse solutions.
Provide detailed documentation, end user training and knowledge-transfer services to customers, and internal teams.
Mentor developers, acting as an SME in data warehouse architecture and data modelling

What You’ll Bring:

Advanced data modelling skills (Star schema, Snowflake schema, data vault)
Proven track-record of building EDW’s
Advanced ETL /ELT processes design and implementation.
Advanced skills in performance tuning, query plan, query plan analysis, indexing, table partitioning.
Strong skills in cloud platforms such as Azure, AWS & GCP
Strong skills in Azure Data Factory and data Flows  and Azure SQL data platform.
Extensive knowledge of Databricks architecture and features.
Proven track-record  in the design, development and implementation of data solutions using Databricks.
Extensive knowledge of Snowflake’s architecture and features.
Proven track-record  in the design, development and implementation of data solutions using Snowflake.
Experience in data ingestion tools such as Apache Kafka, Informatica, AWS Glue, Azure event hubs, Fivetran, Matillion, DBT and Coalesce.
Experience in Apache Airflow.
Strong consultation and clients’ management skills
Strong understanding of Agile delivery methodology.
Excellent verbal and written communications.

 

Required Skills and Qualifications

Bachelor's degree in Computer Science or related discipline
Minimum 8+ years’ experience in EDW design and implementation.
Minimum 8+ years’ experience in ETL architecting and design.
Minimum 8+ years’ experience in data modelling (Star schema & Snowflake schema)
Minimum 5+ years’ experience in semantic layer development.
Minimum 5+ years’ experience in reporting and visualization tools.
Advanced skills in Microsoft BI stack.
Minimum 8+ years’ experience in various Microsoft SQL server technologies including SSIS, SSRS, SSAS
Minimum 4+ years’ experience in design, development and implementation of data solutions using Snowflake.
Minimum 4+ years’ experience in design, development and implementation of data solutions using Databricks.
Wherescape RED, 3D experience is preferred.
Minimum 3+ years’ experience in Power BI.
Advanced skills in Azure, Fabric, and Snowflake pipelines, with experience in tools such as Azure Data Factory, Coalesce, Matillion, dbt, and Fivetran.
Strong skills in data platform implementation, configuration, performance and cost management tuning (i.e. Azure, Fabric, Snowflake).

 

Why join us here at Datacom?

Datacom is one of Australia and New Zealand’s largest suppliers of Information Technology professional services. We have managed to maintain a dynamic, agile, small business feel that is often diluted in larger organisations of our size. It's our people that give Datacom its unique culture and energy that you can feel from the moment you meet with us.

We care about our people and provide a range of perks such as social events, chill-out spaces, remote working, flexi-hours and professional development courses to name a few. You’ll have the opportunity to learn, develop your career, connect and bring your true self to work. You will be recognised and valued for your contributions and be able to do your work in a collegial, flat-structured environment.

We operate at the forefront of technology to help Australia and New Zealand’s largest enterprise organisations explore possibilities and solve their greatest challenges, so you will never run out of interesting new challenges and opportunities.

We want Datacom to be an inclusive and welcoming workplace for everyone and take pride in the steps we have taken and continue to take to make our environment fun and friendly, and our people feel supported.

Permanent Full-Time | Cannon Hill | On-Site Parking | Hybrid Working

Ready to shape the future of customer engagement?

Join a high-performing marketing team where data, technology, and creativity come together to deliver world-class customer experiences. As our Senior Marketing Analyst, you’ll architect innovative data solutions, drive campaign measurement, and champion the marketing technology stack including Braze, Snowflake, Salesforce, and more.

You’ll be hands-on with segmentation, targeting, and analytics, enabling highly personalised, cross-channel campaigns. Your insights will power smarter decisions, and your technical expertise will help us stay at the forefront of marketing innovation.

Why join us?

Hybrid working arrangements for flexibility and balance.
Be part of a team that values innovation, learning, and impact.
Influence the future of customer engagement across Australia, New Zealand, and Canada.
Work with cutting-edge technology and data platforms.
Real opportunities for development and career impact.
Join a brand committed to sustainability and purpose.
Discounts across our stunning product range and hundreds of retailers.

What you’ll do:

Build and deploy campaigns using leading marketing technology platforms
Drive the Braze CEP product roadmap and champion new tech integrations
Develop segmentation, targeting, and automated data flows for campaign success

Proven experience in marketing analytics, campaign measurement, and data architecture
Advanced skills in SQL, Power BI (or similar), and ideally Python or R

Strong business analysis, documentation, and agile delivery practices
Curiosity, collaboration, and a drive for continuous improvement
Your expertise can transform how we connect with customers. Apply now and join our team here at Michael Hill!

Careers with Impact

More than one million Australians trust HESTA with their money. HESTA is a top-performing industry super fund working for real-world impact. We use our expertise and influence to deliver strong long-term returns while accelerating our contribution to a more sustainable world.

HESTA is also an inspiring and rewarding place to work. That's because what we do makes a difference to the lives of our members. The people who work at HESTA are not only exceptional at what they do, they're focused on living and creating a strong organisational culture. We're an industry super fund dedicated to the people who keep our communities going. People who provide some of the best health, education and community services in the world are HESTA members - and we are proud to serve them.





The opportunity - ‘Do what you love, and you'll never work a day in your life' #careerswithimpact

Bring your authentic & passionate self to this exceptional role.

As our fund continues to grow and evolve into the future, we're seeking a talented Analytics Solution Specialist to contribute to the development and management of our distributed analytics platform. This is your chance to make a real impact by creating innovative data solutions that power business decisions.

What You'll Do

• Design and maintain cutting-edge data products that drive business value
• Architect scalable cloud-based data engineering solutions

Your Expertise

• Hands-on experience with cloud platforms (AWS, GCP, Azure)

• Proven ability to communicate complex technical concepts to diverse audiences

Qualifications


• Tertiary qualification in Computer Science, Engineering, or related field

What Sets You Apart


• Experience with modern data architectures (micro-services, event streaming)
• Proven track record in CI/CD and infrastructure-as-code
• Strong background in cloud-based data warehouses
• Experience in superannuation or financial services
• Excellent stakeholder management skills


Benefits that matter and make a difference for our employees

Leave for those moments that matter, an additional 6 days of leave at the end of year, up to 6 days paid volunteer leave, gender neutral paid parental leave of 20 weeks, Gender Affirmation leave, reproductive health and wellbeing leave, Cultural and Ceremonial leave. Access your LSL after 3 years, take AL at half pay, and purchase up to 2 weeks additional leave (just to name a few!).
Your Professional development matters, up to $5k per year professional development and up to 8 days professional development leave, HESTA scholarships and free access to a range of premium learning tools.
Your health and wellbeing matters, free annual flu shots and skin checks, incredible social events throughout the year and a comprehensive employee assistance program available 24/7.
Your financial wellbeing matters, 15% super, financial planning support, end of year payment for all Enterprise Agreement-covered employees, incentivised Employee Referral Program and novated lease options.

We celebrate, value and include people of all backgrounds, genders, identities, cultures and abilities. We welcome and support applications from First Nations people, physically, neuro or culturally diverse, LGBTQI+, and people of any age. We are proud to be WGEA accredited as an Employer of Choice for Gender Equity.

We want all candidates to feel safe, included and provided with the best opportunity to thrive, if you require reasonable adjustments during your application or throughout the recruitment process, please reach out to a member of the Talent team careers@hesta.com.au and we'll call you to discuss.

We'll close applications when we find the right person, so get in quick before you miss this opportunity.

Job Title: Principal Data Consultant
Location: Perth, WA (Hybrid) or Melbourne
Employment Type: Permanent
Salary: $220,000 – $240,000 + Super

About the Role
This is a senior-level data consulting position designed for an experienced data leader who can bridge strategy, delivery, and client engagement. You’ll act as a trusted advisor to clients, guiding them on how to use data, AI, and cloud technologies to solve complex business problems – while also shaping internal capability and mentoring teams.
The role blends leadership, consulting, business development, and technical oversight. You’ll represent the company in Perth’s data community and play a key role in delivering high-quality, value-driven data solutions.

Critical Requirements (Must-Haves)

Minimum 10+ years of experience in consulting, with a significant portion in senior or principal-level roles.
Strong pre-sales experience, including a proven track record of winning work, shaping proposals, and influencing project outcomes.
Deep technical expertise in at least one major cloud/data platform (Azure, Snowflake, Databricks, AWS) — multiple is ideal.
This role requires a rare blend of commercial, consulting, and technical capability.

Key Responsibilities

Leadership & Consulting

Serve as a senior advisor to clients, helping them design and deliver data and AI strategies that create real business impact.
Lead conversations with executive stakeholders to define project goals, architectures, and success outcomes.
Mentor and guide internal data consultants, providing direction and technical leadership.
 
 Business Development

Support the growth of the business by identifying opportunities, shaping proposals, and contributing to client pitches.
Collaborate with senior leaders to define client solutions that align with strategic goals.
Represent the company at industry events, conferences, and community meetups to strengthen brand presence.
 Delivery & Project Oversight

Oversee delivery of complex data projects, ensuring they are delivered on time, within scope, and with measurable value.
Guide technical teams working across modern data stacks (Azure, AWS, Databricks, Snowflake, etc.).
Provide hands-on support where needed, balancing strategy with practical delivery.
 Capability & Product Development

Improve internal frameworks, methodologies, and delivery practices for efficiency and scalability.
Contribute to the development of new data products, accelerators, and service offerings.
 Community & Brand

Act as an ambassador for the organisation within Perth’s data community.
Build and maintain strong client relationships, promoting collaboration and long-term partnerships.
Support internal learning and development through mentoring and knowledge sharing.

About You

10+ years of experience in consulting, delivering large-scale data projects and influencing senior stakeholders.
Demonstrated history of pre-sales success — shaping and winning meaningful work for a consulting business.
Strong technical knowledge across modern data platforms — Azure, AWS, Databricks, Snowflake (one or more required).
Proven track record leading or advising on large-scale data and cloud projects.
Excellent communication and stakeholder management skills; comfortable presenting to executives and guiding teams.
Strategic mindset with the ability to stay hands-on when needed.
Experience in consulting or client-facing environments is highly regarded.

If you’re interested, please email thana@psgaus.com.au.

Job Title: I.T Snr Business Analyst (D365 Supply Chain & Ops)
Ad Text:
About us:
Snackbrands Australia is part of Intersnack Group, a private German snack food company founded in 1968. Although internationally owned we are still very much a local company Creating Happy Snacking Moments for everyone!


Here at Snack Brands Australia, we proudly make some of Australia’s favourite snacks including Kettle, CC’s, Thins, Cheezels, The Natural Chip Company and Nice & Natural. Across our three sites, we make over 200 million packets of chips a year - that's a lot of enjoyment and fun we bring to snackers every day! We encourage a culture that is exciting, challenging and we strive for innovation in everything we do. Our aim is for our people to share in our success, enjoy our products and reap the benefits of their hard work within a supportive environment where work life balance is encouraged!


About the role:


We’re looking for an experienced Senior Business Analyst – Supply Chain Management to join our IT Applications team and drive the successful delivery of D365 projects, enhancements and support across our Operations function.

This role will be based between our head office in Norwest with regular travel to our manufacturing site at Orchard Hills.

What you’ll be responsible for:

Lead analysis, configuration and delivery of Microsoft D365 Operations projects and enhancements
Support supply chain and manufacturing users including production problems, incidents and change requests i.e. manage and resolve open tickets in your support queue.
Follow ITIL processes and methodologies for approval and migration of changes to production
Collaborate with Operations, Project Office and IT teams to resolve issues across operations, manufacturing, warehousing, distribution and inventory.
Partner with supply chain and operations departments across the business to ensure solutions meet operational requirements and align with business milestones.
Coordinate project plans, budgets and reporting.
Influence best practice solution architecture and support a high-performance IT culture.
Work with vendors to provide support and upgrade information.
Develop, execute and lead unit, system and user testing as required to implement changes into production
Build strong relationships across stakeholders and business users. 

What you’ll bring to the role:
Proven experience as a Senior BA in Supply Chain/SCM, ideally in FMCG.
Excellent Dynamics 365 and business process knowledge in the Manufacturing and Supply Chain modules.
Solution knowledge of Dynamics 365, SQL data base and integration technologies.
Excellent communication, stakeholder engagement and influencing skills.
Strong analytical, project planning and commercial acumen.
Ability to manage multiple initiatives, navigate conflicting priorities and work with senior leaders 


What can you expect in return?
A supportive working environment (with plenty of snacks on hand!) where you'll feel engaged and valued, career growth, Birthday Leave, Access to discounts on Retailers, onsite parking (including electric car charging stations) and a focus on health and wellness (like Wellbeing Days!) to make your workplace more enjoyable!



**Our application process includes an Application Form that will be emailed to you directly after your submission. Please ensure you check your junk inbox for this application form, as only applications with this form will be considered. Thank you

For a strictly confidential discussion, please contact Janine Jackson on 0409 802 806. Alternatively, submit your application via the Apply Button or visit www.deanling.com.au

 

Diversity, Equity & Inclusion
We welcome applications from people of all backgrounds, experiences and identities.  By embracing difference, we strengthen teams and create environments where people can genuinely thrive.

EML is a leading Workers Compensation and Personal Injury Claims Management business. Our goal is to help people get their lives back through ongoing support during their return-to-work journey. We continue to experience ongoing growth and now have over 4,000 dedicated employees. We foster a learning culture that allows for us to continually invest in our employees ensuring a long-term career here at EML.

THE OPPORTUNITY

As we expand, our Technology team is growing rapidly, driving innovation in AI for Workers Compensation. We're transforming the industry with cutting-edge solutions that enhance claims management, improve outcomes, and streamline processes.

We’re looking for a bold AI leader to set the vision, shape the strategy, and lead a fast-growing team of researchers, engineers, and data scientists. You’ll own the lifecycle of AI solutions, from concept to deployment, while embedding best-practice governance, reporting & data privacy.

You’ll partner closely with leaders across the business to embed AI into real products and services, turning ideas into measurable outcomes. As the function grows, you’ll continuously optimise models, lift performance, and evolve capability at pace.

This role is as much about people and momentum as it is about technology. You’ll build a high-performing team, develop talent, and steer delivery across multiple initiatives, managing priorities, budgets, and timelines in a rapidly scaling environment.

This will be a permanent, full-time position based in the Sydney office, with flexibility to work from home up to 2 days per week.

YOUR RESPONSIBILITIES

Define and implement AI strategies that align with business objectives and drive innovation. 

Lead the design, development, and deployment of AI models and solutions. 

Oversee project timelines, resources, and budgets to ensure seamless delivery. 

Provide strong leadership, mentorship, and professional development opportunities for the AI team. 

Ensure AI solutions adhere to best practices, including reporting, governance, data privacy, and ethical considerations. 

Collaborate with cross-functional teams to integrate AI into products and services. 

Monitor and optimise AI performance, making data-driven adjustments to improve accuracy and efficiency. 

ABOUT YOU

7 + years leadership experience with a focus on managing a team of AI professionals, including researchers, engineers, and data scientists.

Hands on experience in overseeing AI projects, with a focus on leadership rather than hands-on technical development.

Expertise in developing and implementing AI strategies that align with organisational goals.

Capability to provide mentorship and professional development opportunities for team members.

Ability to stay updated with the latest advancements in AI and machine learning technologies and adapt strategies accordingly.

Solid understanding of AI and machine learning concepts, even if not directly involved in technical development.

Exceptional knowledge of data privacy regulations and ethical considerations in AI development.

A degree in computer science, Artificial Intelligence, Machine Learning, or a related field would be advantageous.

WHAT WE OFFER


We stand together as equals. EML is an equal opportunity employer so by coming to work for us, you will be part of a culture that celebrates diversity and inclusion. We are committed to maintaining a workplace where everyone feels valued and where we show respect, integrity and honesty.


EML provides career opportunities and great employee benefits, including:

A diverse and collaborative team culture like no other

Flexibility to work from home to support work/life balance

A corporate wellbeing program with discounted health insurance and gym membership

Generous discounts from over 350 retailers through our RewardsHub program

Comprehensive learning and development opportunities to help you reach your full potential

Access to support and counselling services with work or personal matters, through our Employee Assistance Program

Companywide events to stay connected and celebrate success

Entitlement to annual company incentive scheme + salary reviews

Up to 16 weeks paid parental leave, plus super



We value our people and are committed to supporting our employees by investing in their professional development and providing generous employee benefits. If this position is of interest to you, please apply now.

CPB Contractors is Australia’s leading contractor and the largest infrastructure construction company in our region. Part of the CIMIC Group, we are proud to be constructing Australia’s future and do so collaboratively with our partners and clients.

We hire for careers, not project life. CPB Contractors has more than 50 major infrastructure projects in delivery, across all key sectors of the construction industry, including roads and bridges, rail, tunnelling, defence, airports, buildings and resources, providing you with career opportunities for years to come.

What can our construction projects build for you?

CPB Contractors along with our industry partners has been selected as preferred proponent to deliver two major packages for the Cross River Rail Projects: the Tunnel, Stations and Development (TSD) package and the Rail, Integration and Systems (RIS) package. Cross River Rail is a new 10.2-kilometre rail line from Dutton Park to Bowen Hills, which includes 5.9 kilometres of tunnel under the Brisbane River and the CBD.

The RIS package is crucial to the overall delivery and success of Cross River Rail, and its integration with the Queensland Rail network.  RIS will be delivered by the UNITY Alliance which brings CPB Contractors, UGL, AECOM and Jacobs together with partners HASSEL, RCS Australia, Acmena, Martinus Rail and WIRED Overhead Solutions to deliver the full scope of works over the next five years. This includes:

Rail civil and electrical works
Brownfield rail surface works primarily to the north of the tunnel, including an upgrade of Exhibition Station and a major augmentation of Mayne Yard
Upgrade of seven suburban stations to the south
Rail operational systems works
Rail signalling works and communication, and integration and commission activities.

Your opportunity

Reporting into the Finance Manager, this role will sit in the project finance team with access to a broad range of finance and operational systems and staff. This role will analyse data from the projects ERP, BI and operational systems and develop meaningful insights for stakeholders across all levels.

Responsibilities will include:

Review of forecasting model to ensure that the UNITY forecast is consolidated in a robust platform, minimising calculation and data errors
Engage with stakeholders to improve their cost reporting and forecasting
Assist in preparing papers for review and approval by the Alliance Leadership Team
Papers are to set out details of spend, forecast and reasons for the project claiming the costs against the Project Owner
Assist in month end activities, primarily assisting with cost reviews to identify and correct any costs that are not reimbursable
Support the Finance Manager with ad-hoc reporting requests

Our minimum requirements for this role are:

Degree qualified in Commerce / Business majoring in Accounting and/or Finance
CA / CPA qualification desirable but not mandatory
Minimum 2 years working in an FP&A / Business Partnering role or similar
Experience working in a large Construction / Engineering / Infrastructure / Property business
Systems experience especially with BI platforms. Recent hands-on experience with BI/JDE an advantage but not mandatory
Advanced Excel and (user friendly) modelling skills
Ability to structure complex data from a variety of sources to develop insights for executive level management
Proven ability to drive process improvements and automation not just in a Finance environment but at an operations / project level
Natural ability to business partner with non-finance teams and build strong relationships
Analytical and inquisitive nature and a desire to always challenge the norm
Commercially savvy with business acumen
Flexible and adaptable to a fast paced and changing environment
Ability to work autonomously and is self-motivated
Strong sense of ethics and values
Experience working hands-on in a project environment desirable but not mandatory
Experience with preparing (or assisting with) budgets / forecasts for large businesses desirable but not mandatory
Experience working in Big 4 / mid-tier accounting firms desirable but not mandatory

 

We particularly welcome and encourage applications from Indigenous Peoples, women, the LGBTQIA+ community, mature workers, Veterans and Active Defence Reserve members, people with disabilities and people from different cultural backgrounds. CPB Contractors is proud to hold the Workplace Gender Equality Agency (WGEA) Citation - Employer of Choice for Gender Equality.

We’re always looking for ways to make CPB Contractors a more rewarding place to work and offer a unique set of benefits, including:

A rewarding career where we support your development, training and promote from within.
Opportunities across all construction sectors so that there is always an opportunity suitable for the next stage in your career.

Please note: This role is being sourced through CPB Contractors directly and we will not accept applications via external recruitment agencies.

There's No Us Without U. Care with Us, for Today and Tomorrow

There's no life without water, and at Urban Utilities, we live and breathe that knowledge every single day. It's why our people are so passionate about what they do and how they do it. And it's why we need people like YOU. Come shape our future with us and make a real and lasting impact across our teams.

Your Opportunity

We have an opportunity in a newly shaped Strategic Asset Data Analyst role in our Infrastructure Planning & Delivery group.

This role sits in our Integrated Planning team, who are essential in shaping the vision and objectives of our policies and servicing strategies. The team is responsible for building, adapting, and implementing plans for catchments, water supply zones, and data systems to define performance targets, establish investment pathways, and develop Strategic Business Cases - all driving an affordable, sustainable, and deliverable portfolio to achieve key objectives.

Reporting to the Leader Strategic Asset Planning, the Strategic Asset Data Analyst supports the design, configuration, testing and application of advanced analytics tools and systems for renewal investment forecasting and asset management as part of the asset planning team.

The Strategic Asset Data Analyst is responsible for utilising engineering and data science, combined with technical asset management knowledge to leverage big data and business intelligence tools to deliver real impact for Urban Utilities.

Some of your accountabilities will include:

Undertake strategic and tactical investment planning scenario analysis and modelling over a 10 - 100-year horizon to enable asset planning and support delivery of our critical outcomes.
Make recommendations to improve data and analytics systems and platforms, contributing to the continuous improvement and refinement of data and analytics strategy.
Contribute to the design and creation of reporting strategies and templates. Lead execution of complex reports, identifying and interpreting complex patterns and trends, and translating those insights into actionable recommendations.
Collect business requirements using a variety of methods such as interviews, document analysis, workshops, and workflow analysis to express the requirements in terms of target user roles and goals.
Contribute to stakeholder engagement through identifying stakeholders, finding out their needs/issues/concern and working through these problems and opportunities in partnership.

About You

We are seeking candidates who are passionate about shaping our future and, ideally, have the following qualifications, skills and experiences:

You have a growth mindset and are highly collaborative. You will pro-actively engage with stakeholders to align objectives and deliver customer and community focussed outcomes.
Relevant general work experience in the water, energy, resources, or industrial sectors, using key intelligence and analytics to inform strategic asset planning.
Experience in managing complex and diverse data science / engineering / advanced analytics tools and systems to generate high value insights and reports for business decision making.
Education in Engineering, Data Science, Data Analytics or specialist work experience and relevant industry knowledge.

At UU, we celebrate diversity. We genuinely believe that bringing together diversity of thoughts, perspectives and expressions is key and crucial to our success as a business. You might find you meet some, but not all, of the job requirements for this role. We'd still encourage you to apply as we we're looking for the right human being for this role - it's about so much more than ticking all the boxes!

Why Urban Utilities?

At Urban Utilities, the work we do is about so much more than the bottom line. We're a leading provider of world-class drinking water and wastewater services to the vibrant communities of Brisbane, Ipswich, Lockyer Valley, Somerset, and Scenic Rim. As we continue to grow, we're committed to planning ahead and shaping a sustainable future around water for generations to come.

At the core of our work lies genuine care: for our team, our customers, communities, and the environment. From the flush of a toilet to major infrastructure projects and residential developments, we're dedicated to being there every step of the way.

Our HQ is in Fortitude Valley, Brisbane, but you'll find us all over SEQ - working in cool places like the SAS Laboratory in Darra, field-based depots in Eagle Farm, Acacia Ridge, Bundamba, and wastewater treatment plants dotted across the region.

We know the chance to thrive, and progress comes hand in hand with the support to balance work with life. So, you'll access an increasingly diverse range of benefits and initiatives that'll help you bring the best you. Speaking of which, here's just a sample of the benefits we offer our team:

Generous Salary Packaging options, including novated leases
Corporate discounts across Health insurance, technology and more
18 weeks of paid parental leave, 15 days personal leave including two proactive wellbeing days, and an additional day of leave each year to connect with friends and family
Flexibility at UU depends on the type of work you do but could include options such as, 9-day fortnights and flexible days. Talk to us about what flexibility means to you!

Visit our website to learn more about us at www.urbanutilities.com.au
